TAE buffer stands for Tris‑Acetate‑EDTA buffer. It is a buffering solution primarily used in agarose gel electrophoresis for separating nucleic acids such as DNA and RNA. The formulation typically contains Tris (tris‑hydroxymethyl‑aminomethane), acetate (derived from acetic acid), and EDTA (ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid), providing optimal pH stability and chelation of divalent cations.

